            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Sarah Sharma\u2019s day begins before the fog has fully retreated from the hills of her West Portal neighborhood. Raised in a practical, middle-class family in suburban Illinois, Sarah\u2019s ambition was always her most defining trait. Her father, an accountant, and her mother, a high school history teacher, instilled in her a formidable work ethic and a quiet curiosity about the world beyond their manicured lawn. This curiosity led her to a degree in marketing and, eventually, an MBA from Northwestern\u2019s Kellogg School of Management.\n\nHer career began in Chicago, but the gravitational pull of innovation and direct-to-consumer brands drew her to San Francisco a decade ago. It was here she met and married Raj Sharma, a brilliant software engineer. Their bond was forged over a shared love for travel and a mutual drive for success. Though their paths diverged five years ago, the divorce was amicable, and she kept his name\u2014it felt like a part of her story, a testament to a significant chapter of her life. They remain friends, occasionally grabbing dinner in the Mission.\n\nNow, as the Director of Global Merchandising for a major apparel company, her days are a blur of spreadsheets, international calls, and trend forecasting. Her 12.8-mile commute on the MUNI Metro is a sacred, non-negotiable part of her routine. It\u2019s her time to disconnect with a podcast or simply watch the city wake up as the train rumbles toward downtown. She cherishes her quiet West Portal flat, a sanctuary from her high-stakes job, and knows the owners of the local bookstore and Italian bakery by name.\n\nSarah has achieved the financial and professional success she once dreamed of, but a new question has begun to surface. While she eyes a potential Vice President role, she also fantasizes about a different path\u2014one with more personal freedom. Perhaps starting her own consulting agency, helping smaller, ethical brands find their footing. At 39, Sarah Sharma stands at a crossroads, proud of the life she\u2019s built and thoughtfully contemplating what the next, more personal, chapter of success will look like in the city she now calls home."
